#function to read in list of files and SUPERMERGE them all


supermerge <- function(listofiles, casefiles){
  
  #get list of dataframes that were read in
  #append each repeat to a wide format
  #and change colnames of repeat to colname 1 colname 2 etc
  #spit out SUPER DF of ALL reapeats to be merged with first DF
  #this will take some time
  #will remain a list of DFs with a universal key "master_row"
  if(1==0){
    #dev mode
    listofiles = lst
    casefiles
  }

    if(length(listofiles)== 1){
    dat <- read.csv(listofiles[[1]], stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
    return(dat)
    }

  #listofiles <- lst
  #exclude meta files
  if(is.na(mean(grepl("meta", listofiles))) == TRUE){
    print("Found meta files, ignoring")
    listofiles <- listofiles[!grepl("meta", listofiles)]
  }

  


  #read in all csvs from direc
  dat <- c()
  for(i in seq(1:length(listofiles))){
    dat[[i]] <- read.csv(listofiles[[i]], stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
    colnames(dat[[i]])
  }
  
  
  #check for any 0 dim files and exclude
  d<- c()
  lf <- c()
  for(i in seq(1:length(listofiles))){
    if(dim(dat[[i]])[1] > 0){
      d[[i]] <- dat[[i]]
      lf<- c(lf, listofiles[[i]])
    }
  }
  dat <- d
  listofiles <- lf
  
  
  print(paste("first file==",listofiles[1]))
  Sys.sleep(3)
  form <- dat[[1]]
  names(form)[1] <- "master_row"

  #formid is unique
  
  for(i in seq(from=2, to=length(listofiles))  ){
    try(names(dat[[i]])[names(dat[[i]]) == 'row.number__0'] <- "master_row")
    try(names(dat[[i]])[names(dat[[i]]) == 'number__0'] <- "master_row")
    #try(names(dat[[i]])[names(dat[[i]]) == 'number'] <- "master_row")
    #form <- merge(form, tmp, by="master_row")
    
  }
  
  
  rm(tmp)
  rm(tmp2)
  rm(blank)
  rm(bln)
  blank <- list()
  
  
   
   

  for(k in seq(from=2, to=length(listofiles))){
    print(paste("stripping:",listofiles[k]))
    xtem = tail(strsplit(listofiles[[k]],"\\/"),n=1)[[1]][length(tail(strsplit(listofiles[[k]],"\\/"),n=1)[[1]])]
    xtem = gsub(".csv", "", xtem)
    xtem = gsub("Repeat- ", "", xtem)
    xtem = gsub("Repeat", "", xtem)
    xtem
    
    dat[[k]][ dat[[k]] == "---" ] <- NA
    dat[[k]] = Filter(function(x)!all(is.na(x)), dat[[k]])

    xyz <- unique(dat[[k]]$master_row)
    blank[[k]] <-data.frame(row.names=xyz)
    rm(bln)
    
    for(i in seq(1:length(xyz)) ){
      #print(xyz[i])
      tmp <- subset(dat[[k]], master_row==xyz[i])
      bln <- data.frame(row.names=xyz[i])
    
      for(j in seq(1:length(tmp$master_row))){
        tmp2 <- tmp[j,]
        colnames(tmp2) <- paste(xtem,colnames(tmp2),j,sep="-")
        bln <- cbind(bln, tmp2)
        #blank[[k]][i,] <- cbind(blank[[k]][i,], tmp2) # nope, doesnt work
      }
      
      names(bln)[names(bln) == paste0(xtem,'-master_row-1')] <- "master_row"
      if(i==1){
        blank[[k]] <- bln
      }
      if(i>1){
        blank[[k]] <- rbind.fill(bln, blank[[k]]) 
      }
      rm(bln)
      #l <- merge(blank[[k]], bln, by="master_row", all=TRUE)
      
    }}
  
  supdat <- form
  cnt <- c()

  
  #blank[[1]]$master
  #take new list and MERGE IT ALL
  for(k in seq(from=2, to=length(listofiles))){
    print(dim(blank[[k]])) 
    supdat <- merge(supdat,blank[[k]], by="master_row",all=TRUE)
    cnt <- c(cnt,dim(blank[[k]])[2])
    
  }
  
  #these two should be equal
  xx1 <- dim(supdat)[1]
  print(paste("merge with cases. Start dim=",dim(supdat)[1]))
  
  findex <- match(find_name(colnames(supdat),"id"),find_name(colnames(supdat),"oaf"))
  name1 <-  find_name(colnames(supdat),"oaf")[findex[!is.na(findex)]][1]

  name2 <-  find_name(colnames(supdat),"site")[1]
  
  supdat$unique_id <- paste0(unlist(supdat[name1]),unlist(supdat[name2]))
  supdat$unique_id
  #supdat$unique_id <- paste0(unlist(supdat[name1]),supdat$Preload_and_Respondent_Selection.site)
  cases <- read.csv(casefiles)
  
  lastdat <- merge(cases,supdat, by="unique_id")
  xx2 <- dim(lastdat)[1]
  
  print(paste("No. rows pre-merge", xx1, "No. rows after caselist merge",xx2))
  print(paste("dropped clients == ", xx1-xx2))
  
  #sum all the dims
  sum(c(cnt,dim(form)[2]))-length(listofiles)+1 # subtract duplicates od master row
  
  
  #clean up useless cols
  xn <- find_name(colnames(supdat), "row.number")
  for(i in xn){
    supdat[i] <- NULL
  }
  
  colnames(supdat) <- gsub("-","_",colnames(supdat))
  
  #remove duplicate columns
  supdat <- supdat[, !duplicated(t(supdat))]
  
  #filter NAs
  supdat <- Filter(function(x)!all(is.na(x)), supdat)
  
  return(supdat)
}



#this function will add plots to the same page
#pretty plots on same page
multiplot <- function(..., plotlist=NULL, file, cols=1, layout=NULL) {
  library(grid)
  
  # Make a list from the ... arguments and plotlist
  plots <- c(list(...), plotlist)
  
  numPlots = length(plots)
  
  # If layout is NULL, then use 'cols' to determine layout
  if (is.null(layout)) {
    # Make the panel
    # ncol: Number of columns of plots
    # nrow: Number of rows needed, calculated from # of cols
    layout <- matrix(seq(1, cols * ceiling(numPlots/cols)),
                     ncol = cols, nrow = ceiling(numPlots/cols))
  }
  
  if (numPlots==1) {
    print(plots[[1]])
    
  } else {
    # Set up the page
    grid.newpage()
    pushViewport(viewport(layout = grid.layout(nrow(layout), ncol(layout))))
    
    # Make each plot, in the correct location
    for (i in 1:numPlots) {
      # Get the i,j matrix positions of the regions that contain this subplot
      matchidx <- as.data.frame(which(layout == i, arr.ind = TRUE))
      
      print(plots[[i]], vp = viewport(layout.pos.row = matchidx$row,
                                      layout.pos.col = matchidx$col))
    }
  }
}

clean_cc <- function(datan, TCvar){
  #drop people with messing T/C vals
  if(length(datan$unique_id) == 0){
    print("making unique id")
    
    a=find_name(colnames(datan), "oaf_id")[[1]]
    b=find_name(colnames(datan), "site")[[1]]
    datan$unique_id = paste0(unlist(datan[a]), unlist(datan[b]))
    
  }

  
  datan = subset(datan, TCvar !="---" )
  datan = subset(datan, unique_id != "---")
  
  for(i in colnames(datan)     ){
    datan[i] <- gsub("---", NA, factor(unlist(datan[i])))
    datan[i] <- gsub("-87", NA, factor(unlist(datan[i])))
    datan[i] <- gsub("-99", NA, factor(unlist(datan[i])))
    datan[i] <- gsub("-89", "unknown", factor(unlist(datan[i])))
  }


  xx1 = dim(datan)[2]
  #filter out cols which are 100% NA
  datan <- Filter(function(x)!all(is.na(x)), datan)
  print(paste("dropping", xx1-dim(datan)[2] , "columns due to all NA"))
  
  trufal = c()
  bina <- c()
  trydate = c()
  trynum = c()
   

  #convert to numeric
  for(ix in colnames(datan)){
    if(is.character(datan[,ix]) == TRUE){
      if(is.nan(mean(as.numeric(unlist(datan[ix])),na.rm=TRUE)) == FALSE  ) {
        print(paste("attempting num conversion",ix))
        datan[ix] <- as.numeric(unlist(datan[ix]))
      }}}  
  
  
  
  #convert string true false to real true false
  for(ix in colnames(datan)){
    if(is.character(datan[,ix]) == TRUE){
      if(isTRUE(unique(datan[ix])[1,]=="False" | unique(datan[ix])[1,]=="True")==TRUE) {
        print(paste("attempting conversion",ix))
        datan[ix][datan[ix] =="False"] <- 0
        datan[ix][datan[ix] =="True"] <- 1  
        datan[,ix] <- as.numeric(datan[,ix])
        trufal <- c(trufal, ix)}}}
  
  
  
  
  #convert string 1 0  to real true false
  for(ix in colnames(datan)){
    if(is.character(datan[,ix]) == TRUE){
      if(isTRUE(unique(datan[ix])[1,]=="0" & unique(datan[ix])[2,]=="1")==TRUE) {
        print(paste("attempting str(true) conversion",ix))
        datan[ix][datan[ix] =="0"] <- 0
        datan[ix][datan[ix] =="1"] <- 1  
        datan[,ix] <- as.numeric(datan[,ix]) 
        bina <- c(bina, ix)
        }
      if(isTRUE(unique(datan[ix])[1,]=="1" & unique(datan[ix])[2,]=="0")==TRUE) {
        print(paste("attempting str(1) conversion",ix))
        datan[ix][datan[ix] =="0"] <- 0
        datan[ix][datan[ix] =="1"] <- 1  
        datan[,ix] <- as.numeric(datan[,ix]) 
        bina <- c(bina, ix)}
      
      }
    
  }  

  
  
  ids <- find_name(colnames(datan),"Date")
  idless <- ids[!grepl("update",ids)]
  print("getting IDs...")
  #ix <- idless[1]
  #ix <- "Harvest_Dates.expected_harvest_date_OAF_Beans"
  for(ix in idless){
    print(paste("checking if date", ix ))
    datan[ix] = gsub("---", NA, unlist(datan[ix]))
    t = na.omit(unique(datan[ix]))
  
    if(t[[1]][1]!= "1" & t[[1]][1] != "0" & sum(grepl("[A-z]", unlist(t)) ) <1 ) {
        datan$temp = unlist(datan[ix])
        datan$temp = as.Date(datan$temp, origin="1970-01-01")
        test = datan$temp
        if(is.na(mean(test, na.rm=T)) == FALSE){
        if(mean(test,na.rm=TRUE)>=16000 & mean(test,na.rm=TRUE)<=18000 ){
          print(paste("attempting date conversion", ix))
          datan[ix]= datan$temp
          trydate = c(trydate, ix)
        
      }}
      datan$temp <- NULL  
      }} 
  
  

  d = datan
  
  acres <- find_name(colnames(datan),"acre")
  trynum <- c()
  for(ix in acres){
    datan[ix] <- gsub("---", NA, unlist(datan[ix]))
    test = as.numeric(unlist(datan[ix]))
    
    if(mean(test,na.rm=TRUE)<= 0.99 & mean(test,na.rm=TRUE)>=0.01 ){
      print(paste("attempting numeric conversion 1", ix))
      datan[ix]= as.numeric(unlist(datan[ix]))
      trynum <- c(trynum, ix)
      
    }
    if(mean(test,na.rm=TRUE)>=1.01 & mean(test,na.rm=TRUE)<=10.0){
    print(paste("attempting numeric conversion 2", ix))
    datan[ix]= as.numeric(unlist(datan[ix]))
    trynum <- c(trynum, ix) }
    }

  

  

  #finally make an easier flag
  #datan[TCvar] = as.numeric(as.character(unlist(datan[TCvar])))
  #ind = as.numeric(as.character(unlist(datan[TCvar])))
  #print(length(ind))
  
  datan$Flag <- unlist(datan[TCvar])
  datan$Flag[datan$Flag==1] = "C"
  datan$Flag[datan$Flag==0] = "T"
  
  #d <- datan
  
  datan = datan[!is.na(datan$Flag),]

  #print some data type checks
  #trufal = c()
  #bina <- c()
  #trydate = c()
  print("shoudl be 1/0")
  try(print(summary(datan[trufal[1]])))
  print("should be 1/0")
  try(print(summary(datan[bina[1]])))
  print("should be reasonable date")
  try(print(summary(datan[trydate[1]])))
  
  print("should be numeric")
  try(print(summary(datan[trynum[1]])))
  
  
  Td = subset(datan, Flag=="T")
  Cd = subset(datan, Flag=="C")
  
  
  return(list(datan,Td,Cd)) }

#this func will plot raw data and output lists of outliers
#macres is the list of vars to interrograte
#byby is the var to group by (for one of the plots) e.g. enumerator ("info.username") or district etc
#harsh is inverse harshness, e.g. =3 will allow more outliers than ==2, 1.5 is about right
plot_vars <- function(macres,datafra, byby, harsh=1.5, filout="./plots",     xys = c("Preload_and_Respondent_Selection.oaf_id","info.username","Preload_and_Respondent_Selection.site","Preload_and_Respondent_Selection.district","Flag")){
  #variable names, dataframe, the ID to summarise by (plot 4), and the "harshness" of outlier detection, higher values mean less outliers
  listfigs <- list()
  library(ggbeeswarm)
  supflagged <- NA
  for(ix in seq(1:length(macres))){
    dir.create(filout,showWarnings = FALSE)
    i <- macres[ix]
    nam <- tail(strsplit(i,"\\.")[[1]], n=1)
    namby <- tail(strsplit(byby,"\\.")[[1]], n=1)
    print("#############################")
    print(paste("analysing", nam))
    
    
    xvals <- unlist(datafra[i]) 
    bwid <- length(xvals)/10
      
    if(is.numeric(xvals)==FALSE){
      xvals = as.Date(xvals)
      datafra[i] = xvals
      
    }

    datafra$temp = xvals
   
    
    summy <- ddply(datafra, c("unique_cluster", "PC_Flag"), summarise,  clustval= mean(temp, na.rm=TRUE ))
    
    #devmode
   #  dt$temp <- unlist(dt["freshweight_oaf"])
   #  sumd <- ddply(dt, c("unique_cluster", "Flag"), summarise,  clustval= mean(temp, na.rm=TRUE ))
    
  
    

    xv <- na.omit(subset(summy, PC_Flag=="C")$clustval)
    if( length(which(xv > 0))  > 15){
    
    if(shapiro.test(as.numeric(summy$clustval))$p.value <= 0.1){
      
      wt <- wilcox.test(as.numeric(subset(summy, PC_Flag=="C")$clustval), as.numeric(subset(summy, PC_Flag=="T")$clustval) ,paired=FALSE, correct=TRUE)$p.value
      pasty <- paste("MWU clustered pval",round(wt,3))
      print(pasty)
    }
    
    if(shapiro.test(as.numeric(xvals))$p.value > 0.1){
      #welch test
      wt <- t.test(as.numeric(subset(summy, PC_Flag=="C")$clustval), as.numeric(subset(summy, PC_Flag=="T")$clustval), alternative = "two.sided", var.equal = FALSE)$p.value
      pasty <- paste("Welch clustered pval",round(wt,3))
      print(pasty)
    }
    }
    
    if( length(which(xv > 0))  <= 15){
      pasty <- "No appropriate H-test"
      
    }

    
    if(mean(as.numeric(unlist(datafra[i])), na.rm=T) <= 15000){
      
      print(nam)
      print(mean(unlist(datafra[i]), na.rm=TRUE))
      print(summary(unlist(datafra[i])))
      print("#########")
      xvals = unlist(datafra[i])
      
      
      p <- ggplot(datafra, aes(x=unlist(datafra[i]), fill=PC_Flag)) + geom_histogram(alpha=.2, bins=10) + xlab(nam)
      p <- p + ggtitle(bquote(atop(.(i), atop(italic(.(pasty)), "")))) 
      #boxplot
      p3 <- ggplot(datafra, aes(x=PC_Flag, y=xvals)) + geom_boxplot() + ggtitle("") + xlab(nam)
      
      #beeswarm
      p2 <- ggplot(datafra) +  geom_beeswarm(aes(x=PC_Flag,y=unlist(datafra[i]) )   ) + xlab(nam) +ylab("")
      
      #by byby
      datafra$tempcol <- as.numeric(unlist(datafra[i]))
      
      #gdat <- datafra %>% group_by(bquote(.(byby))) %>% summarise_each(funs(mean))
      gdat <- ddply(datafra, c(byby), summarise,  newvar= mean(tempcol, na.rm=TRUE ) )
      p4 <- ggplot(gdat, aes(x=newvar)) +  geom_histogram(bins=length(gdat$newvar)/5,colour="black", fill="white") + ggtitle(paste(namby, "averages")) + xlab(nam)
      listfigs[[ix]] <- list(p,p2,p3,p4)
      jpeg(filename=paste0(filout,i,".png"), pointsize =12, quality = 200, bg = "white", res = NA, restoreConsole = TRUE)
      multiplot(p,p2,p3, p4, cols=2)
      dev.off()  
      }
    
    if(mean(as.numeric(unlist(datafra[i])), na.rm=T) >=15000){
      
      print(nam)
      print(mean(as.Date(unlist(datafra[i]), origin="1970-01-01"),na.rm=T))
      print("#########")
      xvals = as.Date(unlist(datafra[i]), origin="1970-01-01")
      
      p <- ggplot(datafra, aes(x=unlist(datafra[i]), fill=PC_Flag)) + geom_histogram(alpha=.2, bins=10) + xlab(nam)
      p <- p + ggtitle(bquote(atop(.(i), atop(italic(.(pasty)), "")))) 

      
      
      #boxplot
      p3 <- ggplot(datafra, aes(x=PC_Flag, y=xvals)) + geom_boxplot() + ggtitle("") + xlab(nam)
      
      #beeswarm
      p2 <- ggplot(datafra) +  geom_beeswarm(aes(x=PC_Flag,y=as.Date(unlist(datafra[i]), origin="1970-01-01")  )) + xlab(nam) +ylab("")
      
      #by byby
      
      datafra$tempcol <- as.Date(unlist(datafra[i]),origin="1970-01-01")
      
      #gdat <- datafra %>% group_by(bquote(.(byby))) %>% summarise_each(funs(mean))
      gdat <- ddply(datafra, c(byby), summarise,  newvar= mean(tempcol, na.rm=TRUE ) )
    gdat$newvar <- as.Date(gdat$newvar, origin ="1970-01-01")
    p4 <- ggplot(gdat, aes(x=newvar)) +  geom_histogram(bins=length(gdat$newvar)/5,colour="black", fill="white") + ggtitle(paste(namby, "averages")) +  xlab(nam)
      
      listfigs[[ix]] <- list(p,p2,p3,p4)
      
      jpeg(filename=paste0(filout,i,".png"), pointsize =12, quality = 200, bg = "white", res = NA, restoreConsole = TRUE)
      multiplot(p,p2,p3,p4, cols=2)
    
      dev.off()  
      }
    
    
    try(dev.off() )
    try(dev.off() )
    
    
    
    xvals = as.numeric(xvals)

    print("outlier detection (beta)")

    if(1==1){
      flagged = c(0,0)
      IQR<- quantile(xvals, 0.75, na.rm=TRUE)[[1]] - quantile(xvals, 0.25, na.rm=TRUE)[[1]]
      cutoff = subset(datafra, xvals <=  quantile(xvals, 0.25, na.rm=TRUE)-(IQR*harsh) )  
      cutoff2 = subset(datafra, xvals >=   quantile(xvals, 0.75, na.rm=TRUE)+(IQR*harsh) ) 
      flagged = rbind(cutoff,cutoff2)
      try(dim(flagged))
      if(dim(flagged)[1]>= 1){
        flagged = flagged[c(xys, i)]
        colnames(flagged) = c(xys, "var_value")
        flagged$variable <- i
        flagged = flagged[complete.cases(flagged),]
        
        supflagged <- rbind(supflagged, flagged)
      }
      print(paste(nam, "Non-normal - Found", dim(flagged)[1],"suspicous values for enumerators"))
    }
    
    
    
  }


  cnt <- c()
  
  for(g in unlist(unique(supflagged[byby]))){
    val = sum(!is.na(which(supflagged[byby]==g)))
    cnt <- c(cnt, val)   }
  
  
  endat = data.frame(byby=unlist(unique(supflagged[byby])), "Total_outliers"=cnt)
  endat <- endat[order(-endat$Total_outliers),] 
  
  write.csv(endat, file=paste0(filout,"Short_summary.csv")  )
  
  

  #supflagged$Date_val = as.Date(supflagged$Date_val, origin="1970-01-01")
  
  write.csv(supflagged, file=paste0(filout,"flagged_values.csv") )
  return(listfigs)
  
  
  kable(endat, format = "markdown", row.names=FALSE, align='c', caption="summary of outliers")
  #kable(supflagged, format = "markdown", row.names=FALSE, align='c', caption="All flagged values")
  
}




#this func will attempt to remove outliers based on some good estimates and then plot data
#macres is the list of vars to interrograte
#byby is the var to group by (for one of the plots) e.g. enumerator ("info.username") or district etc
#harsh is inverse harshness, e.g. =3 will allow more outliers than ==2, 1.5 is about right

find_name <- function(d, nom){
  dx = tolower(d)
  nom = tolower(nom)
  d[grepl(nom, dx)]  }




plot_excoutlierx <-  function(macres,dataframy, byby, harsh, filout){
  #variable names, dataframe, the ID to summarise by (plot 4), and the "harshness" of outlier detection, higher values mean less outliers
  
  library(ggbeeswarm)
  supflagged <- NA
  
  for(ix in seq(1:length(macres))){
    dir.create(filout,showWarnings = FALSE)
    pth = filout
    i <- macres[ix]
    nam <- tail(strsplit(i,"\\.")[[1]], n=1)
    namy <- tail(strsplit(byby,"\\.")[[1]], n=1)
    #find outliers
    xvals <- unlist(dataframy[i])
    xvals = as.numeric(xvals)
    
    
    flagged = NA
    IQR<- quantile(xvals, 0.75, na.rm=TRUE)[[1]] - quantile(xvals, 0.25, na.rm=TRUE)[[1]]
    flagged = subset(dataframy, as.numeric(unlist(dataframy[i])) >  quantile(xvals, 0.25, na.rm=TRUE)-(2*harsh) & as.numeric(unlist(dataframy[i])) <   quantile(xvals, 0.75, na.rm=TRUE)+(2*harsh) )  
    if(dim(flagged)[1]>= 1){
      flagged = flagged[c("Preload_and_Respondent_Selection.oaf_id","info.username",i,"Preload_and_Respondent_Selection.site","Preload_and_Respondent_Selection.district","Flag")]
      flagged$variable <- nam
      flagged = flagged[complete.cases(flagged),]
      print(dim(flagged))
    }
    if(all(is.na(dim(flagged)[1] ))== TRUE){
      flagged=dataframy
    }
    print(paste(nam, "Found and dropped", dim(dataframy)[1] - dim(flagged)[1],"suspicous values "))
    datafra = flagged
    
    ####
    
    
    xvals = unlist(datafra[i])
    
    bwid <- mean(unlist(xvals), na.rm=TRUE)/10
    if(shapiro.test(xvals)$p.value < 0.1){
      wt <- wilcox.test(unlist(subset(datafra, Flag=="C")[i]), unlist(subset(datafra, Flag=="T")[i]) ,paired=FALSE, correct=TRUE)$p.value
      pasty <- paste("MWU pval",round(wt,3))
      print(pasty)
    }
    
    if(shapiro.test(xvals)$p.value > 0.1){
      #welch test
      wt <- t.test(unlist(subset(datafra, Flag=="C")[i]), unlist(subset(datafra, Flag=="T")[i]), alternative = "two.sided", var.equal = FALSE)$p.value
      pasty <- paste("Welch pval",round(wt,3))
      print(pasty)
    }
    
    if(mean(as.numeric(unlist(datafra[i])), na.rm=T) < 15000){
      
      print(nam)
      print(mean(unlist(datafra[i]), na.rm=TRUE))
      print(summary(unlist(datafra[i])))
      xvals = unlist(datafra[i])
      print("#########")
      
      
      p <- ggplot(datafra, aes(x=unlist(datafra[i]), fill=PC_Flag)) + geom_histogram(alpha=.2, bins=10) + xlab(nam)
      p <- p + ggtitle(bquote(atop(.(i), atop(italic(.(pasty)), "")))) 
      #boxplot
      p3 <- ggplot(datafra, aes(x=Flag, y=xvals)) + geom_boxplot() + ggtitle("") + xlab(nam)+ylab("")
      
      #beeswarm
      p2 <- ggplot(datafra) +  geom_beeswarm(aes(x=Flag,y=unlist(datafra[i]) )   ) + xlab(nam) +ylab("")
      
      #by byby
      datafra$tempcol <- as.numeric(unlist(datafra[i]))
      
      #gdat <- datafra %>% group_by(bquote(.(byby))) %>% summarise_each(funs(mean))
      
      gdat <- ddply(datafra, c(byby), summarise,  newvar= mean(tempcol, na.rm=TRUE ) )
      p4 <- ggplot(gdat, aes(x=newvar)) +  geom_histogram(bins=length(gdat$newvar)/5,colour="black", fill="white") + ggtitle("Enumerator averages") + xlab(nam)
      multiplot(p,p2,p3, p4, cols=2)
       jpeg(filename=paste0(pth,nam,".png"), pointsize =12, quality = 200, bg = "white", res = NA, restoreConsole = TRUE)
       multiplot(p,p2,p3, p4, cols=2)
       dev.off()  
    } 
    
    if(mean(as.numeric(unlist(datafra[i])), na.rm=T) >=15000){
      
      print(nam)
      print(mean(as.Date(unlist(datafra[i]), origin="1970-01-01"),na.rm=T))
      print(summary(as.Date(unlist(datafra[i]), origin="1970-01-01")))
      print("#########")
      xvals = as.Date(unlist(datafra[i]), origin="1970-01-01")
      
      p <- ggplot(datafra, aes(x=unlist(datafra[i]), fill=PC_Flag)) + geom_histogram(alpha=.2, bins=10) + xlab(nam)
      p <- p + ggtitle(bquote(atop(.(i), atop(italic(.(pasty)), "")))) 
      
      
      #boxplot
      p3 <- ggplot(datafra, aes(x=Flag, y=xvals)) + geom_boxplot() + ggtitle("") + xlab(nam) +ylab("")
      
      #beeswarm
      p2 <- ggplot(datafra) +  geom_beeswarm(aes(x=Flag,y=as.Date(unlist(datafra[i]), origin="1970-01-01")  )) + xlab(nam) +ylab("")
      
      #by byby
      
      datafra$tempcol <- as.Date(unlist(datafra[i]),origin="1970-01-01")
      
      #gdat <- datafra %>% group_by(bquote(.(byby))) %>% summarise_each(funs(mean))
      gdat <- ddply(datafra, c(byby), summarise,  newvar= mean(tempcol, na.rm=TRUE ) )
      gdat$newvar <- as.Date(gdat$newvar, origin ="1970-01-01")
      p4 <- ggplot(gdat, aes(x=newvar)) +  geom_histogram(bins=length(gdat$newvar)/5,colour="black", fill="white") + ggtitle("Enumerator averages") +  xlab(nam)
      
       multiplot(p,p2,p3,p4, cols=2)
       jpeg(filename=paste0(pth,nam,".png"), pointsize =12, quality = 200, bg = "white", res = NA, restoreConsole = TRUE)
       multiplot(p,p2,p3,p4, cols=2)
       dev.off()  
      
      }
    
    
    try(dev.off() )
    try(dev.off() )
    
    
  }
  
  
  
}

15 Rough estimates of beans acres

Please note, these estimates are derived through two steps:

  • Get the fraction of beans land by dividing the self-reported maize acres by self-reported beans acres

  • Apply this fraction to the actual GPS measurement of maize land

This obviously means we cannot be sure of the quality of these estimates. Additionally, we know from the PC survey that control farmers are more likely to overestimate their land sizes than control farmers, suggesting that our estimate here will also be biased.

The below is the average beans acreage for all farmers (beans or no) planted beans (i.e.excluding farmers who do not plant beans and farmers we havent yet surveyed).

dat$OAF_beans_frac <- dat$LE_form.Land_Estimates_Survey.OAF_Maize_Beans_Intercrop_Acres / dat$LE_form.Land_Estimates_Survey.OAF_Maize_Acres

dat$nonOAF_beans_frac <- dat$LE_form.Land_Estimates_Survey.NonOAF_Maize_Beans_Intercrop_Acres / dat$LE_form.Land_Estimates_Survey.NonOAF_Maize_Acres


dat$OAFbeans_acres <- dat$OAF_beans_frac * dat$total_OAF_maize_GPSacres
dat$nonOAFbeans_acres <- dat$nonOAF_beans_frac * dat$total_nonOAF_maize_GPSacres

dat$OAFbeans_acres[is.na(dat$OAFbeans_acres)]<-0
dat$nonOAFbeans_acres[is.na(dat$nonOAFbeans_acres)] <- 0




Treat <- subset(dat, PC_Flag=="T")

Treat$new = "OAF Land"
